title: Can't Buy Happiness
lyrics:
And I crouch in the snow
Don't wanna let the moment go
Kiss me on the tip of my nose
Come home to my freshly folded up clothes
I take the time that I'm given

Blame it on myself

Sitting here reminiscing about the times that we've had

Times that were lost

And I guess I'm holdin' on



'Cause I only ever wanted to feel free

'Cause money can't buy, buy all my happiness

And don't you know I tried

And I tried all of this

And it don't mean a thing



No it don't mean

No it don't mean

No it don't mean



No, no, no
